# Mnemo Wiki — Schema & Conventions

## Purpose

Personal knowledge base compiled automatically from Claude Code sessions via the
Karpathy LLM Wiki pattern. Updated by the Mnemo plugin Stop hook and the
`/mnemo:wiki-save` slash command.

## Taxonomy

Organise pages under `wiki/` using subdirectories:

| Path | For |
|---|---|
| `wiki/projects/<name>.md` | Per-project notes, decisions, status |
| `wiki/concepts/<topic>.md` | Technology concepts, patterns, how-tos |
| `wiki/infra/<service>.md` | Infrastructure, deployment, ops |
| `wiki/inbox/` | Unclassified entries — review and re-file periodically |

## Frontmatter conventions

Every page in `wiki/` must have:

```yaml
---
tags: [<taxonomy-tag>, ...]
updated: YYYY-MM-DD
project: <name>    # omit for cross-project concept pages
---
```

## Entry conventions

- Pages use `[[page-name]]` links to related pages (check index.md for candidates).
- Machine-generated drafts (`auto: true`) in `raw/auto/` are supplementary context
  only — the compiler treats them as lower-confidence than human-reviewed `raw/` entries.
- Never include credentials, API keys, secrets, or connection strings.
- Keep pages atomic and scannable: one clear topic per page.

## Seed pages

Bootstrap with these pages on first compile (if wiki/ has no pages yet):

- `wiki/projects/default.md` — general project notes
- `wiki/concepts/setup.md` — environment and toolchain setup
